Blackstone Group Plans Investment in Turkish Assets, Sabah Says

-- B y   E r c a n   E r s o y
-- 
2011-03-18T06:58:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/blackstone-group-plans-investment-in-turkish-assets-sabah-says.html
  Blackstone Group LP (BX) , the world’s
largest private-equity firm, plans to invest in Turkey’s energy,
retail, health-care and real-estate businesses,  Sabah  reported,
citing an unidentified company official.  The U.S.-based firm hired Kemal Kaya, the former chief
executive officer of Koc Finansal Hizmetler AS, a joint venture
between  Koc Holding AS (KCHOL)  and  Unicredit SpA (UCG) , as CEO of its Turkish
operation, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ercan Ersoy in Istanbul at 
 eersoy@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
 bkammel@bloomberg.net . 